                    "name": "Biology 9 Standard",
                    "track": "school",
                    "level": "S",
                    "description": "This is a standard level Biology course for the 9th grade students. It gives students the opportunity to experience Biology before making their choices in grades 10, 11 and 12, and to develop skills and interest within the scope of Biology disciplines. The topics covered include: Ecology and Evolution. After learning this course, students should know the basic terms and general ideas of Ecosystem and Biogeography, and learn how living things react to their environments, what the history and \"rule\" of Evolution is. This course will also use lab practices, field studies, and seminars to help students build critical thinking and grasp basic experimental technique that will be used and expanded on in future Biology courses.",
