                    "name": "Biology 9 Honors",
                    "track": "school",
                    "level": "H",
                    "description": "This is an honors level Biology course for the 9th grade students. It gives students the opportunity to experience Biology before making their choices in grades 10, 11 and 12, and to develop a deeper understanding of Biology-specific lab skills and thought processes. The course develops student understanding in the areas of Ecology and Evolution. Though using the same textbook, this Honors Biology course differs significantly from the standard level course in Biology with respect to the range and depth of topics covered, the type of laboratory work done by students, and the time and effort required of students. Students are required to understand about Darwin's Theory of Evolution, Evidence of Evolution, Patterns and Processes of Evolution, Nutrient Cycle and Energy Flow in the Ecosystem, and Basic Concepts of Ecology. Through daily homework assignments, lab experiments, projects, and regular exams, students will gain the knowledge of Evolution and Ecology and the ability of scientific inquiry and reasoning.",
