                    "track": "school",
                    "level": "H",
                    "description": "This is a 10th grade Honors Biology course designed to be taken by students who intends to undertake IB/AP Biology in their junior years, Though using the same textbook, this Honors Biology course differs significantly from the Standard level course in Biology with respect to the range and depth of topics covered, the type of laboratory work done by students, and the time and effort required of students. Students in this course are required to study topics including Biochemistry, Cell Biology, Genetics, and Biotechnology in greater depth, and to study additional topics aligned with the IB/AP Biology. By carrying out laboratory work, students are encouraged to develop important skills such as detailed observation, accurate recording, experimental design, manual manipulation, data interpretation, statistical analysis, and operation of technical equipment. This two-semester course will provide students with the conceptual framework, factual knowledge and analytical skills necessary for the IB/AP Biology. Successful completion of this course is a prerequisite for IB and AP Biology.",
