                    "name": "Environmental Engineering 11",
                    "track": "school",
                    "description": "Environmental Engineering is the branch of engineering that is concerned with protecting people from the effects of adverse environmental effects, such as pollution, as well as improving environmental quality. This course is designed for students who are interested in environmental issues and the scientific principles involved. The course includes energy mechanics, conservation of energy, heat and work, environmental issues like air pollution, global warming and thermal pollution, different types of traditional energy sources and alternative energy sources. The goal of this course is to provide students with the basic physical principles behind the different energy transformations, to seek potential solutions to environmental issues arising from energy use, to understand the environmental, social and economic tradeoffs that must be made and to improve students' environmental awareness.",
