                {
                    "id": "BIO111E040",
                    "name": "IB Biology SL Y1",
                    "track": "IB",
                    "level": "SL",
                    "description": "The IB Biology program is structured into two tiers: Standard Level (SL) and Higher Level (HL). In the recently revised curriculum for the 2025 assessment, both SL and HL students engage with a shared core syllabus and a unified scientific investigation framework. This new syllabus is organized around four key themes: Unity and Diversity, Form and Function, Interactions and Interdependencies, and Continuity and Change. These overarching themes are further delineated into four levels of biological organization, namely Molecules, Cells, Organisms, and Ecosystems. The designed curriculum fosters the cultivation of specific skills, attributes, and dispositions. While the fundamental skills and practical activities in Biology remain consistent for both SL and HL students, those pursuing HL are expected to delve deeper into certain topics through the exploration of additional higher-level (AHL) materials. The primary difference between SL and HL lies in the scope and intensity of the subject matter. This course is geared towards highly motivated students who are eager to embrace intellectual challenges. By studying IB Biology, students gain insights into the scientific community's collaborative work ethos and communication practices. Emphasis is placed on the practical application of the scientific method through hands-on experimental work. It is mandatory for all students enrolled in an IB subject to take the external exam at the conclusion of Year 2.",
